## Neon Database (`neonctl`)

- This project uses Neon serverless Postgres. Project: `flow-state` (ID: `hidden-hall-84768725`), region: `aws-eu-central-1`.
- `neonctl` is installed globally. Always pass `--project-id hidden-hall-84768725` and `--output json`.
- Use Drizzle for app schema changes (`pnpm db:generate` then `pnpm db:migrate`). Use `neonctl` only for exploration or out-of-band fixes.
- Test schema changes on a temporary branch first — never run untested DDL on main.
- Never run destructive SQL (DROP, DELETE without WHERE, TRUNCATE) without explicit user confirmation.
- Connection strings are secrets — never echo them. Reference by env var name (`DATABASE_URL`).
- Neon MCP is configured at `.cursor/mcp.json` — use it for structured queries when available.
